    <!-- ACC Config Tooltips -->
    <string name="capacity_control_info">- SHUTDOWN: automatically shutdown the system at/below this battery level when battery is not charging.&lt;br /&gt;- STOP: and RESUME capacities dictate when charging should stop and resume, respectively.&lt;br /&gt;- CHARGING SWITCH is the control file, plus ON and OFF values for switching charging on/off. By default, ACC uses whatever works.</string>
    <string name="power_control_info">- Every reduction in peak charge voltage of 0.10V/cell is said to double the cycle life.&lt;br /&gt;- Unfortunately, not all devices/kernels support this feature.</string>
    <string name="temperature_control_info">- This disables charging for set seconds to cool the battery&lt;br /&gt;- COOLDOWN TEMP depends on COOLDOWN RATIO.&lt;br /&gt;- MAX TEMP pauses charging; it resumes at RESUME TEMP.</string>
    <string name="cooldown_info">- Charging ON/OFF ratio in seconds (e.g., 50/10) - reduces battery stress induced by prolonged high temperature and high charging voltage by periodically pausing charging.&lt;br /&gt;- If charging is too slow, turn this off or change the ratio to something like 50/5.&lt;br /&gt;- When disabled, COOLDOWN CAPACITY and COOLDOWN TEMP values have no effect.&lt;br /&gt;- This functionality is a fair alternative to the charging voltage limit feature.</string>
    <string name="on_plugged_info">This is used for updating control files whose contents change on certain power events (e.g., plug/unplug). It is particularly useful for enforcing custom max voltage/current for usb/wireless charging.</string>
    <string name="battery_idle_info_label">This allows supported device to draw power directly from the external power supply when charging is paused.</string>
    <string name="miscellaneous_info_label">Various acc configurations that did not fit in other defined categories</string>

